
Step 1. go to: http://www.pygame.org/download.shtml
	download: pygame-1.9.1release-python.org-32bit-py2.7-macosx10.3.dmg 12MB

Step 2. download the 32 bit version of python if you do not already have it. look in /usr/local/bin for 32 bit versions of python. run the game with this. 
	example: first_game$ /usr/local/bin/python2.7-32 game.py 
	OR: How to specify python executable with venv: virtualenv -p /usr/bin/python2.7 venv

RESOURCES

- http://www.raywenderlich.com/24252/beginning-game-programming-for-teens-with-python

USAGE

$ /usr/local/bin/python2.7-32 game.py

